{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:Buddha statue elephant rock.JPG|thumb|right|300px|The statue of the Buddha on top of the Elephant rock.]]
[[File:Ethagala.JPG|thumb|View from the top of Ethagala|600px]]
'''Ethagala''' (ඇතාගල) (the '''Elephant Rock''') is one of seven [[rock (geology)|rocks]] that overlook the town of [[Kurunegala]], in [[Sri Lanka]]. The rock face reaches {{convert|316|m}} over the town and in its shape resembles a crouching [[elephant]], which explains the rock's name.
{{commonscat|Ethagala}}

