''[[Inside Out (2015 film)|Inside Out]]'' is a 2015 American [[3D film|3D]] [[computer animation|computer-animated]] [[comedy-drama]] [[adventure film]], co-written and directed by [[Pete Docter]]. The film is set in the mind of a young girl named Riley Andersen ([[Kaitlyn Dias]]), where [[Emotion#Classification|five personified emotions]]—Joy ([[Amy Poehler]]), Sadness ([[Phyllis Smith]]), Fear ([[Bill Hader]]), Anger ([[Lewis Black]]), and Disgust ([[Mindy Kaling]])—try to lead her through life as she moves to a new city and has to adjust to her new life.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Seitz|first1=Matt Zoller|title=Inside Out Movie Review & Film Summary (2015) {{!}} Roger Ebert|url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/inside-out-2015|accessdate=July 31, 2016|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|date=June 18, 2015}}</ref> After premiering it at the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival|68th Cannes Film Festival]] on May 18, 2015, [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]] released the film theatrically in the United States on June 19, 2015. Made on a production budget of $175 million,<ref name="budget">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/box-office-inside-out-wont-stop-jurassic-world-rampage-1201522202/|title=Box Office: 'Inside Out' Won't Stop 'Jurassic World' Rampage|first=Brent|last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 17, 2015|accessdate=June 18, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618090429/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/box-office-inside-out-wont-stop-jurassic-world-rampage-1201522202/|archivedate=June 18, 2015|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''Inside Out'' grossed a worldwide total of $857 million, making it the [[2015 in film|seventh highest-grossing film of 2015]] and the [[List of highest-grossing films|49th highest-grossing film of all time]] as of July 2016.<ref name="BOM2015">{{cite web|title=2015 Yearly Box Office Results|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2015&p=.htm|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=March 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/ | title=All Time Worldwide Box Office Grosses | publisher=Box Office Mojo | accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref> [[Rotten Tomatoes]], a [[review aggregator]], surveyed 317 reviews and judged 98% to be positive.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/inside_out_2015/|title = Inside Out|publisher = [[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate = December 12, 2015}}</ref>

''Inside Out'' won [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]] and was nominated for [[Academy Award for Best Original Screenplay|Best Original Screenplay]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]]. It also received a [[BAFTA Award for Best Animated Film|BAFTA Award]], [[Golden Globe Award for Best Animated Feature Film|Golden Globe Award]], [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Animated Feature|Critics' Choice Award]], [[New York Film Critics Circle Award for Best Animated Film|New York Film Critics Circle Award]], [[Satellite Award for Best Animated or Mixed Media Feature|Satellite Award]], and [[Saturn Award for Best Animated Film]]. The film led the [[43rd Annie Awards]] with fourteen nominations, and won ten awards,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Coggan|first1=Devan|title=Inside Out wins top prizes at the Annie Awards|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/02/07/annie-awards-2016-winners-list|accessdate=June 4, 2016|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=February 7, 2016}}</ref> including [[Annie Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]], [[Annie Award for Directing in a Feature Production|Outstanding Achievement in Directing in an Animated Feature Production]] for Docter and [[Annie Award for Voice Acting in a Feature Production|Outstanding Achievement in Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production]] for Smith.

The [[American Film Institute]] selected ''Inside Out'' as one of its ten Movies of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.afi.com/here-are-the-afi-awards-2015-official-selections/|title=Here Are the AFI Awards 2015 Official Selections|publisher=[[American Film Institute]]|date=December 16, 2015|accessdate=December 16, 2015}}</ref>

