{{unreferenced|date=September 2017}} This is a '''[[list of extinct languages]] of [[Europe]]''', languages which have undergone [[language death]], have no [[native speakers]] and no [[Historical language|spoken descendant]]. As the vast majority of Europeans speak [[Indo-European languages]], a result of the westward portion of the prehistoric [[Indo-European migrations]], the bulk of the [[Paleo-European languages|indigenous languages of Europe]] became extinct thousands of years ago without leaving any record of their existence as they were superseded by [[Celtic languages|Celtic]], [[Italic languages|Italic]], [[Germanic languages|Germanic]], [[Balto-Slavic languages|Balto-Slavic]], [[Hellenic languages|Hellenic]], and [[Iranian languages|Iranian]] Indo-European languages. A small minority of these extinct languages, however, survived long enough to be [[Attested language|attested]].
On the other hand, many European Indo-European languages themselves, such as [[Gothic language|Gothic]], have also become extinct. In some cases however, it is not known whether a language has a spoken descendant or not. For example, because of the uncertain origin of the [[Albanian language]] — aside from its being an Indo-European language — and because little remains of the ancient languages in question, it is disputed whether [[Dacian language|Dacian]], [[Thracian language|Thracian]] or [[Illyrian languages|Illyrian]] have a spoken descendant, Albanian. And because of the scarcity of the evidence, it is not known whether [[Basque language|Basque]] is a descendant of the [[Aquitanian language]].
Although the [[Pomeranian language]] has a spoken descendant, the [[Kashubian language]], the other dialects of Pomeranian are extinct.
==Balkans== {{columns-list|colwidth=120pt| *[[Hellenic languages|Hellenic]] **[[Yevanic language|Yevanic]] **[[Doric Greek]] **[[Ionic Greek]] **[[Aeolic Greek]] **[[Attic Greek]] **[[Arcadocypriot Greek]] **[[Mycenaean Greek]] **[[Pamphylian Greek]] **[[Locrian Greek]] **[[Ancient Macedonian language|Ancient Macedonian]] *[[Italic languages|Italic]] **[[Dalmatian language|Dalmatian]] **[[Pannonian Romance]] *[[Turkic languages|Turkic]] **[[Bulgar language|Bulgar]] **[[Pecheneg language|Pecheneg]] *[[Slavic languages|Slavic]] **[[Old Church Slavonic]] *[[Indo-European languages|Indo-European]] **[[Dacian language|Dacian]] **[[Thracian language|Thracian]] **[[Illyrian language|Illyrian]] **[[Istrian Albanian]] **[[Liburnian language|Liburnian]] **[[Paeonian language|Paeonian]]
*[[Unclassified language|Unclassified]] **[[Eteocretan language|Eteocretan]] **[[Eteocypriot language|Eteocypriot]] **[[Minoan language|Minoan]] **[[Pelasgian language|Pelasgian]] **[[Bryges|Brygian]] **[[Dardani]]
}}
