 specials include "LeAnn Rimes in Concert," "Ray J in Concert with Brandy," "Jonny Lang in Concert" and "Cleopatra in Concert." "'N Sync in Concert" was credited by RCA Records, 'N Sync's label, with significantly boosting sales of the group's self-titled album (Billboard 8/15/98).</ref> || 1997 || 2001 || 2001–02 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''2 Hour Tour''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/nobodys-angel-featured-in-disney-channels-new-reality-music-documentary-series-2-hour-tour-coming-to-los-angeles-77280022.html |title=Nobody's Angel Featured in Disney Channel's New Reality Music-Documentary Series, 2 Hour Tour, Coming to Los Angeles – NULL |publisher=Prnewswire.com |date=November 18, 1999 |accessdate=July 28, 2014}}</ref> || 1998 || 2000 || 2000 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Bug Juice]]'' || {{dts | 1=1998 | 2=2 | 3=28}} || {{dts | 1=2001 | 2=10 | 3=15}} || 2001; 2004; 2006 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Totally Circus]]'' || {{dts | 1=2000 | 2=6 | 3=16}} || {{dts | 1=2000 | 2=9 | 3=24}} || 2000 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Totally Hoops]]'' || {{dts | 1=2001 | 2=1 | 3=7}} || {{dts | 1=2001 | 2=4 | 3=15}} || 2001 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Totally in Tune]]'' || {{dts | 1=2002 | 2=6 | 3=23}} || {{dts | 1=2002 | 2=8 | 3=18}} || 2002; 2006 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[PrankStars]]'' || {{dts | 1=2011 | 2=7 | 3=15}} || {{dts | 1=2011 | 2=12 | 3=16}} || 2011 || |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Code: 9]]'' || {{dts | 1=2012 | 2=7 | 3=26}} || {{dts | 1=2012 | 2=9 | 3=28}} || 2012; 2016|| |- | scope="row" style="text-align:left;" | ''[[Walk the Prank]]'' || {{dts | 1=2016 | 2=4 | 3=1}} || {{dts | 1=2016 | 2=11 | 3=10}} || 2016–18 || Moved to Disney XD full-time |}
