[[File:TriBrataKamchatka.jpg|thumb|right|The Tri Brata]] '''Tri Brata''' ({{lang-ru|Три Брата}}; literally: "three brothers") is a set of three [[Rock (geology)|rock]]s at the entrance to the [[Avacha Bay]]. This picturesque [[stack (geology)|stack]], or [[kekur]], is considered a symbol of [[Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky]].
Local lore suggests that they are three brothers who went to defend the town from a [[tsunami]] and turned to stone. {{Commonscat|Three Brothers Rocks}} {{coord|52.8931|N|158.689|E|source:kolossus-nlwiki|display=title}}
